, they exacerbate income inequality in poor regions. Based on this insight, the book presents a theory on the conditions under which EU funding will enhance well-being. Crucially, it argues the case for enhancing the inclusivity of EU growth, which yields the promise of a more legitimate and stronger union.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Feb 2023) 0aExpenditures, Public. 0aWell-beingxEconomic aspectszEuropean Union countries. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Comparative Politics.2bisacsh1 aRothstein, Bo, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBristol UP/Policy Press Complete eBook-Package 2021z978311119675640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781529217483423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781529217483/original  a978-3-11-119675-6  Bristol UP/Policy Press Complete eBook-Package 2021b2021  aGBV-deGruyter-alles